## Repository structure
```
src/
  api/          # HTTP handlers
  domain/       # Business logic (no framework dependencies)
  infra/        # DB, external API clients
  jobs/         # Background workers
tests/
  unit/
  integration/
docs/
```

## How to run locally
```bash
# Install
npm install         # or: pip install -e ".[dev]" / go mod download

# Environment
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in required vars — see .env.example comments

# Start
npm run dev         # or: make dev
```

## Testing
```bash
npm test            # unit tests
npm run test:int    # integration tests (requires local DB)
npm run test:e2e    # end-to-end (requires running app)
```
Coverage target: **≥80% on domain/ and api/**.

## Key conventions
- **Branching:** `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/` prefixes; PRs target `main`
- **Commits:** Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:` etc.)
- **Error handling:** Never swallow errors; always log with context
- **Secrets:** Never hardcode. Use env vars or AWS Secrets Manager
- **Migrations:** Backwards-compatible only; no destructive changes without a rollback plan

